Below are the Week 5 American Family Insurance ALL-USA Western Washington Girls Performers of the Week. Please send any outstanding stats to HSSports@king5.com for consideration. Be sure to vote for the top performer below, and share your preps photos and videos with us on social media using #K5Preps. The best ones will be shown on TV! 
Vote as many times as you would like. Voting ends Monday, Oct. 19 at noon. 
Elise Petit, Redmond volleyball. Petit had two monster games last week. Against Woodinville, Petit recorded 30 kills, setting a new school kill record, and 19 digs. Later in the week Petit had 22 kills, 20 digs, three service aces, and two solo blocks in the losing effort to Newport. 
Jessica Brennis, Snohomish volleyball. The senior was Snohomish’s go-to hitter when the Panthers came from behind to beat Lake Stevens. Brennis had 28 kills, four service aces and nine digs against the Vikings. She also had 13 kills, 11 digs, and three service aces over Mariner. <!-- iframe --> 
Kiley Lewis, Auburn Mountainview volleyball . Lewis led the charge for Mountainview with over 40 kills in two games last week. The Boise State commit had 24 kills and 11 digs against Enumclaw , and she added 20 kills, five digs, and four blocks against Bonney Lake. Auburn Mountainview volleyball tops Enumclaw 3-1 
Camille Murphy, Holy Names girls soccer. Holy Names’ lead goal scorer tallied three goals and two assists in the Cougars’ win over Nathan Hale. Murphy now has 10 goals and 10 assists this season. 
Sydney Kuehn, Cedarcrest girls soccer. Kuehn scored the Red Wolves’ only goal in double overtime against King’s, handing the Knights their first loss in league play and making Cedarcrest tied for first in league.
